{"@context": "http://schema.org", "@type": "Movie", "url": "/title/tt0076740/", "name": "Sorcerer", "image": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNTVhMzk3ZDItNDIxMi00OTJiLWI3ZmMtMzAwNTQ0YjRhZWZhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjUwMzI2NzU@._V1_.jpg", "genre": ["Adventure", "Drama", "Thriller"], "contentRating": "PG", "actor": [{"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0001702/", "name": "Roy Scheider"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0187337/", "name": "Bruno Cremer"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0704719/", "name": "Francisco Rabal"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0024849/", "name": "Amidou"}], "director": {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0001243/", "name": "William Friedkin"}, "creator": [{"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0338396/", "name": "Walon Green"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm1064118/", "name": "Georges Arnaud"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0018588/"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0023400/"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0005073/"}], "description": "Sorcerer is a movie starring Roy Scheider, Bruno Cremer, and Francisco Rabal. Four unfortunate men from different parts of the globe agree to risk their lives transporting gallons of nitroglycerin across dangerous Latin American...", "datePublished": "1977-06-24", "keywords": "dynamite,remake,remake of french film,building explosion,blowing out a tire", "aggregateRating": {"@type": "AggregateRating", "ratingCount": 18382, "bestRating": "10.0", "worstRating": "1.0", "ratingValue": "7.7"}, "review": {"@type": "Review", "itemReviewed": {"@type": "CreativeWork", "url": "/title/tt0076740/"}, "author": {"@type": "Person", "name": "DB-08-DB"}, "dateCreated": "2002-12-01", "inLanguage": "English", "name": "Lost Classic", "reviewBody": "Sorcerer is a unique, brutal, brilliant film burdened underneath a terrible, wholly unappropriate title. Watching this film, it is not only easy to see why the film was both a huge financial and commercial disaster, it is downright obvious. This is the most un-american/ hollywood/ commercial film backed by a major studio I have ever seen. It is a tough, gruelling 126 minutes that goes nowhere fast, yet holds you firm in its tight grip and beats you senseless throughout. I was exhausted when the film finally arrived at it's rather downbeat ending. The multi-national cast is faultless. Scheider is magnificent. This is an exceptionally demanding, difficult role and he hits it head on, creating an anti-hero who is very, very real: desperate, frightened and desructable. Taking this role, at the height of his fame, was either very brave or very stupid. I'm going with brave. His performance here is a million miles away from his work on Jaws and Jaws 2, yet equally compelling. The photography is in a league of it's own (I only wish the DVD came with an original 2:35:1 print, assuming there is one, as the current disc is presented in a 4:3 full frame), and the music from Tangerine Dream complements the vision perfectly. This is a brilliant piece of film making from the most daring decade of cinema, made by one of cinema's true unpredictable's. Tense, dazzling, dark and fresh, this is an underated film that deserves to be re-evaluated."}, "duration": "PT2H1M", "trailer": {"@type": "VideoObject", "name": "Sorcerer", "embedUrl": "/video/imdb/vi2039677209", "thumbnail": {"@type": "ImageObject", "contentUrl": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BM2JiNGRkZDctNDA1MC00YmMyLWI4NWItM2NlZjU2MjQzODg1XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzU1NzE3NTg@._V1_.jpg"}, "thumbnailUrl": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BM2JiNGRkZDctNDA1MC00YmMyLWI4NWItM2NlZjU2MjQzODg1XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzU1NzE3NTg@._V1_.jpg", "description": "Theatrical Trailer from Universal Pictures", "uploadDate": "2008-04-11T14:51:28Z"}, "cast_and_character": [{"actor": {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0001702/?ref_=tt_cl_t1", "name": "Roy Scheider"}, "character_and_episodes": [{"url": "/title/tt0076740/characters/nm0001702?ref_=tt_cl_t1", "name": "Scanlon"}, 